comment:
Its important to note,  there is a 3 year Statute of Limitations, on a perjury case in California, BUT the mistake people make with that is,  its 3 years from the time the lie was discovered, not stated.   Since the lie just came out with this trial, or i should say lies, as amber has made several, they would have 3 years from feb 2021ish, to begin press charges.

Its also important that, the UK case was against the Sun, and amber was NOT named as a defendant, as such amber could not be compelled to produce evidence or even testify.  

This case is about ambers direct involvement in writing a story, that was in direct violation of a NDA issued by the judge, and ambers actions directly affecting Depp's job.

Its also important to note that,  the UK trial did not have access to a TON of information due to ambers legal team pulling the same tricks they have tried in this case including stalling, claiming things are not available, and essentially requiring the courts to step in and DEMAND every last piece of evidence.    Depp for example will request phone record,  the request will be sent, ignored, sent, ignored, sent, ignored...   after weeks, they have to go to the court, and the court demands the items under discovery, then the laywers argue why it can't shouldn't be, sent...  this delay tactic meant only a small amount of evidence was available to depp in UK... 

Due to covid, and a judge who isn't putting up with delay tactics, discovery has been extended, so things like Bodycam footage showing amber lied,  statements that bruises were actually makeup, and such...  are being brought in.

comment:
Isn't calling 911 considered filing a police report? IF so, wouldn't the claims on the call be considered as such? Also wouldn't she still be held ultimately responsible for that call/filing since she asked her friend to call on her behalf...to whom she gave the description in the first place. It also seems like even that was a set-up by her to potentially have plausible deniability of filing false as she didn't technically make the call, because if she could take the time to give the friend the details, she could have just given those details to the 911 person......

I couldn't care less about either person. In this I am paying some attention because IF one or the other or both were fired simply due to the mess, that would be a HUGE blow to EVERYONE's personal and civil rights in the US. I can see possibly it being argued that the company could lose money by retaining them in a film, but at the same time the person could argue that;
1) That is their personal life which has nothing to do with the company
2) That their personal actions did not directly impact the company in a negative way, meaning if the person is under contract does that affect all of the company's ventures or just the project the person might be working on at the time?
3)) It should fall under discrimination laws, as it could be argued the company could lose revenue due to a person being a particular religion, creed, etc., meaning a person could choose not to see something because they oppose to a certain person within the film...the same applies here. Some won't care and watch no matter any scandal, some will and some won't watch the film because of the topic, some will and some won't because they do/don't agree with certain things a person, involved in the film, has done or said, etc.
